cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.DS, cs.CV, cs.CL 

This paper discusses the practical analysis of XGBoost, a machine learning technique, in terms of training speed, generalization performance, and parameter setup. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper compares XGBoost with other techniques such as random forests and gradient boosting, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The comparison also involves image and text data, which could indicate that it belongs to cs.CV (Computer Vision) and cs.CL (Computation and Language).
